 Lagos State Governor, Mr Akinwunmi Ambode on Thursday had a closed door meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari inside the Presidential Villa, Abuja. Informed sources said that Ambode went to seek audience with the President again to seek his opinion on his second term bid. However, our Correspondent reported that governors under the platform of APC, met on Wednesday night in Abuja, and had on behalf of Ambode, sought the intervention of President Buhari in the APC crisis in Lagos State. It was reported that the Chairman of the APC Governors’ Forum, Gov. Rochas Okorocha of Imo State, delivered the governors’ message to President Buhari, few minutes before his meeting with Ambode. Reports have it that the president may also meet with other party stakeholders in Lagos State within the week towards finding a lasting solution to the crisis.  